<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Infra on Kevin wang's blog</title><link>https://kevinwang930.github.io/tags/infra/</link><description>Recent content in Infra on Kevin wang's blog</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 12:58:16 +0200</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://kevinwang930.github.io/tags/infra/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>K8s generals</title><link>https://kevinwang930.github.io/post/infra/k8s/</link><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 12:58:16 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://kevinwang930.github.io/post/infra/k8s/</guid><description/></item><item><title>K3s generals</title><link>https://kevinwang930.github.io/post/infra/k3s/</link><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 12:20:28 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://kevinwang930.github.io/post/infra/k3s/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;K3s is a lightweight Kubernetes distribution. Minimal footprint, single binary, stripped of non-essential components. Perfect for edge, IoT, and local dev. Fast startup, minimal memory.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Minikube generals</title><link>https://kevinwang930.github.io/post/infra/minikube/</link><pubDate>Sat, 16 May 2026 22:24:23 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://kevinwang930.github.io/post/infra/minikube/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Minikube runs Kubernetes locally in a VM or container. It’s fast, lightweight, and ideal for dev, testing, and learning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="quick-start"&gt;Quick Start&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;minikube start &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# default&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;minikube start --driver&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;docker
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;minikube start --cpus&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;4&lt;/span&gt; --memory&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;8192&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;minikube status &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# check status&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;kubectl cluster-info &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# info&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;minikube stop &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# stop&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;minikube delete &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# delete&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;minikube dashboard &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# UI&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;minikube ip &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# get IP&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;minikube ssh &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# shell&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deploy app:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;kubectl create deployment hello-minikube --image&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;kicbase/echo-server:1.0
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;kubectl expose deployment hello-minikube --type&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;NodePort --port&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;8080&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;kubectl get svc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;minikube service hello-minikube
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="driver"&gt;Driver&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Docker:&lt;/strong&gt; Fast, low overhead, easy setup, works on Linux/macOS/Windows. Needs Docker running. Best for dev and CI.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>